bio.experienceSummary:
I have many years of experience caring for children of all ages. I am looking to obtain part-time babysitting jobs in the afternoon, evenings and some weekends. I love to teach the children new things, do crafts, explore outside with them and most of all create amazing bonds.
 I want to be able to provide parents with comfort and security of having someone trustworthy watching their little ones.

I absolutely love children. I've worked as a camp counselor, a nanny, and as a teacher at early learning centers. I am a mom and understand the importance of trust and safety when it comes to your child's caregiver. I treat every child I care for as my own and love to introduce them to different experiences, such as music. I've been playing guitar for 20 years and singing for even longer. I also implement the RIE philosophy and Reggio philosophy in my caregiving.

description.displayText:
We've had a number of different nannies for my son (now a little over 2) and Bridget has been by far the most outstanding nanny we've ever had. She is easy to communicate with and extremely professional in how she approaches the job, always punctual if not early, and pitches in so that we can end our work day in a restful home. 

Our son loves her because she patiently reads books to him (even making a good effort on the non-English books!), sings songs, comes up with fun sensory and art activities, and generally treats him respectfully and includes him in all care giving, in line with the RIE philosophy. It really makes a difference in how independent he feels, which benefits all of us.

Our setup was that Bridget would bring her own daughter (4 years old) with her through the summer. The two children had a great time together and if they ever did clash, Bridget always set boundaries fairly and firmly. 

I'm going on maternity leave for a few months but would rehire her in a heartbeat.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi! I'm Tayyabah! I am a reliable, responsible, and devoting caregiver who you can completely trust to take care of your children and ensure their safety. I am a college student majoring in Supply Chain Management who likes to bake, watch movies, and go for walks! I have been caring for children for over eight years and have experience taking care of children of all ages and personalities. I can do and help with various activities that your child may require. When I'm there, you can relax and expect to have your children under the best care a parent could wish for.

Hi! I'm a mother myself of two older girls, ages 26 and 24 both of which were preemies. I am extremely reliable, caring, and nurturing and will be sure to treat your children as if they were my own. I have just recently finished with a wonderful family that I have been with for about 3 years but the family is relocating out of state. Prior to having my own children, I worked in a pediatric office for five years. Feel free to leave a message for me with any questions you should have. Thank you.

description.displayText: Our family loves Lori!  We've been so lucky to have her with us for 2.5 years.  She is everything you'd want as a parent in a nanny - responsible, communicative, punctual, loving and caring.  She sees our kids as hers and treats them the same - reinforcing our schedules and house rules - a true extension of us when we're not there. We couldn't be happier to have found her.

bio.experienceSummary:
I am the mother of four grown children. I am interested in providing my services an expertise to assist parents in babysitting their own children. My genuine love and maternal instincts are truly an asset that any parent would appreciate from a caregiver to their loved one. 

I believe in positive reinforcing, challenge your child through conversation and games and yet being calm, patient and understanding.

I have also worked in the medical field for over 20 years, so my experience with handling all situations is another attribute that would help make parents extremely comfortable with me!

I am interested in 4 full days or 2 full days 8-10 hrs each. Sept 2025 looking forward to a new venture

description.displayText: There are many things I could say about Donna, but most importantly, we trust her with our three young children.  It was not easy for me to find someone I could say that about.  Donna is an experienced mother and has young grandchildren, so she knows what she is doing!  She is comfortable caring for children when they are sick, and is capable of making day to day decisions that are in their best interest.  My children love Donna, and are very comfortable with her and therefore so are we!  Donna is also VERY punctual.  Happy to discuss further by email or phone.

bio.experienceSummary: Hello! My name is Story, and I am a reliable and nurturing caregiver with over 5 years of experience caring for children of all ages. I am passionate about creating safe, fun and engaging environments for kids, whether it's helping with homework, playing games or finding creative ways to be active. I'm also happy to assist with light housekeeping, meal preparation and errands to help make your life a little easier. I am also a pet lover and would be happy to care for them as well. Parents love that I am dependable, responsible, and focused on making every experience positive for their children. I'd love to support your family in any way I can!

Hello everyone!

I have experience with kids on all ages so i'm able to provide a safe and rich environment and understand their needs depending on the stage they are so you won't have to worry about them while i'm on guard!

I consider myself a very positive, reliable, fun, creative and very patient person who loves being around little ones, plus I follow the idea of gentle parenting style.

Communication is a key for me and i'll keep you posted on how the shift is going and can do extra chores that are need it upon request.

description.originalText: Laura was absolutely fantastic taking care of our 18month old boy. She came right in, listening to everything we had to share about his schedule, and had him laughing and in her arms within minutes. She fed him, played around the house, and bathed him before putting him down for bed. She kept us updated while we were out with cute pictures of him. We would definitely recommend her for any family looking for someone both caring and super reliable.

bio.experienceSummary: I'm single with no children, but I love children. It's so fun to be with them. Children is a precious gift from the Lord. Babysitting for kids is where my heart is. I am trustworthy, honest, responsible, dependable, helpful, energetic and fun-loving nanny. I have 15 years of experience as a full time nanny assisting kids for all ages.

description.originalText: Oce cared for our 1.5 year old daughter full time for a month. She was full of energy for our active little girl! We really appreciated Oceâ€™s flexibility - she was always on time and willing to come early/stay late when my work schedule changed. Very glad we found Oce!

bio.experienceSummary:
I have experience with children through baby sitting and nanny. I have love and compassion for children. I will take care of them like my own children. I will cook, I will clean, l will bathe them if the parents wants me to. I will take them outside and to the park. I will help with homework. I will do grocery and laundry, I will drop them off to school and pick them up from school. I also have my own car. 
I am a very nice person and understanding. I listen and learn new things everyday. You will not regret having me.

description.originalText: Linda is amazing. She goes beyond what you need & my kids loved her! I would definitely use her babysitting services again! Thank you.
